forward 'one history that fits all' been less workable. Theorizing Historical Consciousness sets various theoretical approaches to the study of historical consciousness side-by-side, enabling us to chart the future study of how people understand the past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aHISTORY / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh1 aLaville, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLetourneau, Jocelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenz, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoisan, Sabrina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRusen, Jorn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalber Phillips, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeixas, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSejxas, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimon, Roger I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimon, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTorpey, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWertsch, James V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268261040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442682610423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442682610/original  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBoo